The paper presents a new approach for transferring dynamic robot control policies from simulation to real hardware, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The approach involves system identification, policy learning, and optimization, which are all common topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of trajectories and Bayesian optimization, which are techniques commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and control systems (cs.SY).
